VARIABLE VROEPOTION
;
NUMBER 22
NAME GM Control Room
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room is in construction.  The end goal is to have all the temp
scripts and other various variables accessible through here.  You
notice that there is a monitor here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 903
IFLOGIN
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
    MOVE 201
    ECHO PLAYER You've been relocated to Andor.
    GMMSG %N just logged into the GM control room and had %h butt moved.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ 0
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
    CLEARVERB
    KILL PLAYER
    POSITION LAY
    GMMSG %N was just killed for reading the monitor in the control room.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
|
Control Room Status:   GM Tools Set (Others may be loaded as well)
Avaiable Control Sets: Tools (@comp controlt.scr)
                       Status Reports (@comp controls.scr)
                       Player Inquiries (@comp controlp.scr)

1) Lens replacement. A GM can touch a lens without danger. Just @add 1669
   and hand to player who had theirs improperly lost.  If they did something
   ingame (like touching it) where losing it was their own fault, they will
   need to redo it.

2) To create a potion, just say its name without any punctuation.

3) To create a foraged herb, say its name without any punctuation or articles.

TECH TOOLS

4) If a player has been interacting with Technology in a positive manner,
   their tech rating should be raised.  Set ADDTECH to the amount to be
   raised (Almost always 1 or 2, never more than 3) and then set SETPLAYERTECH
   to their player #.

5) If you need to set a player's tech rating to 0, set TECHZERO to
   the playernumber of the person to be zero'd out.

6) All tech members should have some tech knowledge.  To seed a person
   with tech knowledge, set RANDOMTECH to player number.
   
Avoid compiling these needlessly, as they use some RAM. Loading one
will NOT unload others).  They ARE here for you to use, however and
if you need to use one, don't hesititate to do so.

If you have other things you wish put in here, please let me know.

*DESCRIPTION_END
;
